p width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uronaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ronaan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand High Poobah</span><br>  Posts: 2401<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 1:10:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11565.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://ronaan.homestead.com/files/125.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I have outgrown my 1hb - so where to now?</span><hr size=1> I'd say SoM is the fastest, and easiest to get, at that stage.<br><br>it's also pretty common, and can be farmed to your heart's content. <p><a href=http://www.monkly-business.com>[60 Grandmaster]</a> <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=592>Brother Ronaan</a> <a href=http://www.wolfsclan-eq.de>< Wolfsclan ></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wubao>Wubao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1506<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 1:15:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11565.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ?</span><hr size=1> &quot;so buying an SoS etc is out.&quot;<br><br>Ok. Don't buy it. Camp it.<br><br>&quot;Here is the question - which weapon(s) should I camp (with guildies obviously)? SoM, Bors, Ad club, katar, ulak?&quot;<br><br>Katars and Ulaks are hand to hand weapons. They won't help skill up your 1hb.<br><br>If you've outgrown your GSC, what is it you're using right now?<br><br>At 56 you can get, with a little work, some luck and some help from friends, an Adamantite Club or a Sceptre of Mastery.<br><br>But the club requires keys and the sceptre requires a raid.<br><br>I think your best bet is the Stave of Shielding. And it can be acquired with just one 6 person group in Chardok. Some amazing XP, and some great loot for your friends as well. Very enticing.<br><br><br>Your question confuses me.<br><br>Probably because I think you're selling your 12/23 a tad short in regards to how useful it actually is. I doubt you've outgrown it, since the only options that are better than it are either very high end, or something like a Stave of Shielding, a Jade Mace or an exquisite velium battlehammer.<br><br>Of course you could just quest the Whistling Fists and have a great 12/20 h2h weapon for free.<br><br>-Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukimonawindfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimona Windfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 620<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 1:27:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11565.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I think your best bet is the Stave of Shielding. And it can be acquired with just one 6 person group in Chardok. Some amazing XP, and some great loot for your friends as well. Very enticing.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Yep. Get thee to Chardok. It should be fantastic exp at your level. Plus you got a shot at an SoS, BoRS, pipe if you don't have it already and a bunch of other cool stuff. Camp Chardok and don't leave until you get what you want. That's what I did. Also, don't worry about losing Chardok faction because you eventually want to get a Spirit Wracked Cord. You can get to ally to Di'Zok after about a week or so in Droga. Not too bad in my opinion. <p><p align="center"><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=511" target="_blank" style = "text-decoration:none;" title="You are now inspecting Kimona..."><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~larry1015/_uimages/sig1.jpg"></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uijusth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ijusth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1825<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 1:55:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11565.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ?</span><hr size=1> Kimona you must be clairvoyant LOL  since I was thinking exactly about faction and am in the process of doing the droga/nurga thing.  Got my yellow robe so don't care about the pipe.  Given faction concerns I would rather build UP dragon killing in Kael and trying for the sceptre rather then going DOWN faction in chardok.  <br><br>Am I wrong in thinking that SoM is close to Bors?  If I get an SoS I might just buy that since they go for 4k on Sayryn (last time I checked) and that would only delay my haste fund a week or two. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukimonawindfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimona Windfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 621<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 2:38:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11565.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ?</span><hr size=1> My opinion is that you should wait to 60 until doing Chardok faction only because the exp in Chardok is so good. Personally I levelled in Chardok and banged out a few AAs before making the switch. Now, I'll admit that Chardok just happens to be my favorite exp zone so I might be a little biased. I also wanted to camp my own SoS because I am tremendously cheap. I don't like to buy an item if I can get exp while camping it. That's just me though.<br><br>If I remember correctly, a SoM will outdamage an SoS in everyday usage, so definitely use the SoM if you got one. But an SoS is still a great item to keep around because of the effect. Back in the day (pre-Tranquil Staff), I used my epic fist + SoM, switch in the SoS to proc Major Shielding (75hps, some MR and some AC, stacks with everything except a shaman's focus buffs, I think), switch the SoM back in and continue with the carnage. I still pop in my SoS today for the effect even though I use a 2hb almost exclusively. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uijusth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ijusth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1826<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 3:06:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11565.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ?</span><hr size=1> Isn't xp in Kael going to be as good as dok?  Also I was comparing som to bors since I know som&gt;sos.  If you only kill chodiaki and skellies will that hit brood faction (might be tought to avoid sarnaks hits LOL)? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushadizasilverclaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadiza Silverclaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 3:39:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11565.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ?</span><hr size=1> Anything you kill in chardok, dog, skel, whatever, is the same factions. <p><a href="http://www.deadlyvirtues.com/" target="_blank"><img src="http://signature-designs.com/images/shadiza3.jpg" border="0"></a><br><a target="new"href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42192">Shadiza Silverclaw</a>, Grandmaster<BR><a target="new"href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=188338">Katya Silverpelt</a>, Hierophant<BR>Deadly Virtues ~ Mithaniel Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukimonawindfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimona Windfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 622<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/24/02 3:46:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11565.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Isn't xp in Kael going to be as good as dok?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->No. Since Kael is considered a city zone the ZEM isn't very good. On the other hand, Chardok is considered a dungeon where the ZEM is higher. I know that with the addition of the Chardok quests, Chardok <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> can</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be looked at as a city zone too, but it was considered a dungeon long before that. At least, that's how it was explained to me by the guildie who first showed me around Chardok. So take that with a grain of salt, it may or may not be true. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Now, keep in mind, I'm only offering my opinion here. I'm not trying to tell you what to do, I'm only offering up what I did. Kael is still a fun zone with lots of interesting stuff in it. Especially if you're looking at increasing your CoV faction. Your first Arena raid will be a blast (provided you have enough people to prevent a wipe). Kael has lots of unique mobs and items, not to mention the Thurg armor pieces. I just think that you're missing out on some fun exp killing greens in Droga while you could be murderizing sarnaks. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>PS. All mobs in Chardok are on Di'Zok faction, including the various chokidais and undead mobs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uijusth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ijusth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1827<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/25/02 8:42:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11565.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ?</span><hr size=1> Already been on 1 Kael raid and it was a blast.  Unfortunately we broke up just as I was getting the hang of splitting the PoZ so I wasn't able to try for my sceptre.  Thanks for the heads up on the xp rates.  Maybe I will hold off then and just sell my salts and skins (was told in bazaar that someone was offering 5k for 80 salt and 40 skins!!!) or save 'em for later.  Those cords are soooo damn tempting though.  No thurg armor really will help me a lot (I am now in acrylia/grey flesh) but the other drops and cov faction help matter.<br>Good thing about droga/nurga is that getting help there will be much easier then arranging a Kael raid.  I can get low 40 support and pl lowbie guildies while I get faction hits and in exchange I get all loot (skin/salt).<br><br>Decisions/decisions <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=11565.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showNextMessage?topicID=11565.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11565.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.emailToFriend?topicID=11565.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.threadControl?topicID=11565.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11565.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=11565.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.